The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses,
and share prices are as of the close in Lima.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose for the first time in seven
days, gaining 0.9 percent to 20,680.89. The MSCI All Peru Capped
Index climbed 1 percent to 2,655.75.  Cia. Minera Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based
silver and zinc mining company, rose 2.1 percent to 48 centimos
after zinc futures advanced in  London , said  Jorge Ramirez , a
trader at Lima-based brokerage Coril SAB.  Sociedad Minera El Brocal SAA (BROCALC1 PE), a zinc and
copper producer, gained 2.1 percent to 49.60 soles after
contract workers ended a 32-day strike.  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peruâ€™s biggest copper
producer, climbed 1.8 percent to $28.70 after copper rebounded
